What is Personal Information?
For the purposes of this Privacy Policy, personal information is any information which you provide to us which personally identifies you, such as your name, email address or billing information, and, in certain circumstances, your location and route information or other data which can be reasonably linked to such information by Wavve.
What Personal Information Do We Collect?
Your use of the Services and/or the Website may involve our collection of certain personal information. The information Wavve collects, and how the information is used, depends on how you choose to use our Services and how you manage your privacy controls.
Account Information
We may collect information used to set up an account, such as your name or email and information you choose to share with Wavve, such as boating routes you chose to save to your account. In some cases, we may collect billing information when you sign up for our Services.
Social Media
If you choose to use your Facebook account as your Wavve account, you may choose to share with Wavve and/or other users information from your social network account, such as your name and social media profile picture.
Information collected when on our Website
You can visit our Website without telling us who you are or revealing any information about yourself, including your e-mail address. However, we may collect personal information about you when you visit our Website through cookies, with your consent. Our collection of personal and other information through cookies is governed by our Cookie Policy. For more information, visit our Cookie Policy
