Information collected when using our Services
Depending on your device and account settings, we may collect, use, process, disclose, transfer, retain and store information about your location. This may include your location while using the Services for boating navigations, and the last location before exiting the app. We use location information to provide you features of the Services. You can enable or disable location Services when you use the Services at any time, through your electronic device.
Information collected when corresponding with Wavve
We collect the personal information that you choose to submit to our Website, such as your name, email address and any other contact, or other information that you choose to provide, including through your use of the “Get In Touch” section of our Website. We collect similar personal information if you choose to correspond with a Wavve representative via e-mail.
When you request information from us, we may use the e-mail address that you provide to send you information about offers on products and services that we believe may be of interest to you. If you have asked us to put you on an e-mail mailing list to provide you with certain information on a regular basis, or if we send you information about our offers on products and services by e-mail, you may ask us to remove you from the list at any time by using the unsubscribe instructions provided with each e-mail, or by contacting us at community@wavveboating.com.
Why Do We Collect, Use, and Disclose Personal Information
Wavve does not sell your personal information.
Your personal information collected is used and disclosed for our business purposes, including:
• to present the Website and its contents to you;
• to provide you with information, products, or services (including Wavve Boating and Wavve Clubs) that you request from us;
• to open and manage your Wavve Boating or Wavve Clubs Account;
• to allow you to use navigation features, interactive features, social media, or other features on the Services, including community features;
• to monitor, improve, and customize our Website, the Services and our customer relationships and experiences;
• to meet regulatory requirements;
• to enforce our Terms and Conditions; and
• to comply with other legal or regulatory obligations.
Your personal information is shared with our employees, contractors, consultants, affiliates and other parties who require such information to assist us with (1) establishing, maintaining and managing our relationship with you, (2) providing features of the Services and/or Website, and (3) improving and customizing the Services and/or Website.
Your personal information may be disclosed or transferred to another party in the event of a change in ownership of, or a grant of a security interest in, all or a part of Wavve.
Wavve may disclose your personal information to other users of the Services when you choose to use interactive features, social media, or similar features on the Services, including community features to share Content, join a group, or make/accept a fleet request.
Wavve may also disclose your personal information to third parties (1) in an emergency that threatens an individual’s life, health, or personal security; (2) when we require legal advice from a lawyer or other professional; (3) for the purposes of collecting a debt or for protection from fraud; (4) in the event of a Dispute; and (5) when otherwise permitted or required by law or in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
Wavve’s Website and Services are not directed to children under the age of 16 and we do not knowingly collect personal information from minors (i.e. anyone under the age of 16). If you are a parent or guardian and you are aware that your minor has provided us with personal information, please contact us at accounts@wavveboating.com.
If we become aware that we have collected personal information from minors without verification of parental or guardian consent, we will take steps to delete or destroy such personal information.
We may collect, use, or disclose your personal information without your knowledge or consent where we are permitted or required by applicable law or regulatory requirements to do so.
Where Do We Process and Maintain Your Personal Information?
Your personal information may be transferred to and maintained outside of your province, state, country or other jurisdiction where the data protection laws may differ than those from your jurisdiction.
If you are located outside Canada and provide us your personal information, please note that we transfer your personal information to Canada and process and maintain it there.
Integration with Social Networks
You may choose to share information between your Wavve account and your social network account. Through this option, you may choose to have personal information and other content about you available from social networks, transmitted and shared through the Services.
By setting your Wavve Account to integrate with social networks, including by signing onto Wavve by using your social network account, you agree to share information (including personal information) between Wavve and such social networks, for the purposes provided under this Privacy Policy.
When you connect to the social network account through the Services for the first time or otherwise make the Services interact with your social network account, you will be asked by the social network to permit the social network to share your personal information stored on such social network with Wavve. We collect your information from your social network account only in accordance with the permissions granted by you (such as your name, email address, profile picture and other information available via the applicable social network).
You understand and agree that the Services may access, make available and store such information so that it is available on and through your Wavve Account, until your Wavve Account is deleted.
How Long Do We Retain Your Personal Information?
Except as otherwise permitted or required by applicable law or regulation, we generally only retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes that we collected it for.
We will keep your Wavve account data until you choose to delete it and/or update it. For example, if you choose to record a boating trip to your account and later delete it, the data is also removed from Wavve’s system. We do not retain it.
If you do not delete Wavve account data, we will keep that data for the lifetime of your Wavve account if it is useful for helping us understand how users interact with our features and how we can improve our Service.
In some cases, personal information will expire after a specific period of time as we set retention timeframes based on the reason for the data’s collection.
Certain information is retained for up to seven years for limited purposes, such as for satisfying legal, accounting or reporting requirements.
How Is Your Personal Information Protected?
Wavve maintains physical, technical and procedural safeguards that we believe are appropriate to the sensitivity of the personal information in question. These safeguards are designed to prevent your personal information from loss and unauthorized access, copying, use, modification or disclosure.
Unfortunately, no data transmission over the Internet can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. As a result, while Wavve strives to protect your personal information, we cannot warrant the security of any personal information you transmit to us, and you do so at your own risk. Once Wavve receives your transmission, we make commercially reasonable efforts to ensure its security on our systems. You can help keep your data safe by taking reasonable steps to protect your personal information against unauthorized disclosure or misuse.
The security of your personal information is important to us. Please contact us at accounts@wavveboating.com immediately of any incident involving the loss of or unauthorized access to or disclosure of personal information that is in our custody or control.
Updating Your Personal Information
It is important that the personal information contained in our records is both accurate and current. If your personal information happens to change during the course of our relationship, please keep us informed of such changes.
In some circumstances we may not agree with your request to change your personal information and will instead append an alternative text to the record in question.
Access to Your Personal Information
You can ask to see the personal information that we hold about you. If you want to review, verify, delete, or correct your personal information, please contact us at accounts@wavveboating.com. Any communication regarding your personal information must be in writing, and you must provide sufficient detail to identify your personal information and the specific correction, verification, or information sought.
If we cannot provide you with access to your personal information, we will inform you of the reasons why, subject to any legal or regulatory restrictions.
What Other Information Do We Collect and How Do We Use It?
In addition to personal information, we may also collect, use, process, disclose, transfer, retain and store other information or Content that you provide while accessing or using the Services or Website, in accordance with this Privacy Policy and Wavve’s Terms and Conditions.
Log Data
When you access the Services by or through an electronic device, we collect certain anonymized additional information automatically, including the type of mobile device you use and other statistics, such as the interaction of your device with our Service, including crash reports (“Log Data”).
We use third party services such as Firebase that collect, monitor and analyze Log Data, including to improve the Services’ functionality.
Watercraft Information
If you choose to provide it to us, we collect, use, process, disclose, transfer, retain and store information about your watercraft.
We use watercraft information for the purposes set out above, including to establish, maintain and manage our relationship with you, to provide you features of the Services, and to improve and customize the Services.
